1
00:00:05,310 --> 00:00:08,050
You have one new message.

2
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:09,930
This is your realtor.

3
00:00:09,930 --> 00:00:13,320
Your electronic payment for
last month's rent has not come through.

4
00:00:13,610 --> 00:00:17,500
Please make your payment to our account
by the end of the week at the very latest.

5
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:23,230
Hakamada Yukio
Attorney at Law

6
00:00:31,610 --> 00:00:33,710
Tokiwa Publishers

7
00:00:32,380 --> 00:00:33,490
Kanae-san!

8
00:00:33,710 --> 00:00:37,080
Hakamada's assistant
Nonomura Kanae

9
00:00:33,720 --> 00:00:35,100
It's your serial's one-year anniversary.

10
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:36,300
Congratulations.

11
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:37,610
Thank you very much.

12
00:00:37,830 --> 00:00:40,360
Plus, look at this reader
survey from last month.

13
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:41,560
You're in third place.

14
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:43,390
3rd place: "Divorce Chaser" Nonomura Kanae

15
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:43,390
Monthly Manday March Issue:
Author Popularity Rankings Based on Reader Survey

16
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:42,610
Wow!

17
00:00:42,610 --> 00:00:44,660
This is the third consecutive month
you've been ranked third, too!

18
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:46,620
You're a full-fledged,
popular manga illustrator

19
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:48,250
and contributor to
Monthly Manday, now.

20
00:00:48,250 --> 00:00:49,530
Nonomura-sensei.

21
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:51,900
Oh, don't call me that, please.

22
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:55,270
Chief editor of Tokiwa Publishers
Ueki

23
00:00:53,190 --> 00:00:54,530
Nonomura-sensei,

24
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:58,370
Would you be interested in doing a serial
for the weekly publication of Manday?

25
00:00:58,650 --> 00:01:00,310
Weekly Manday?

26
00:01:00,310 --> 00:01:01,310
As you already know,

27
00:01:01,310 --> 00:01:03,770
it's Tokiwa Publishers'
powerhouse manga magazine.

28
00:01:03,770 --> 00:01:06,620
We publish five times the number of
issues of the monthly publication.

29
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:09,960
Your monthly serial is highly
regarded by our readers.

30
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:12,420
You can now move up as a
professional manga illustrator.

31
00:01:12,420 --> 00:01:15,790
Editor at Tokiwa Publishing
Tabata Misato

32
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,610
Of course you'd have to end the
current serial, which is too bad.

33
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:16,780
In the final episode,

34
00:01:16,780 --> 00:01:19,060
we want you to reveal
the protagonist's past,

35
00:01:17,090 --> 00:01:19,220
You will be divorcing
your husband, then?

36
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:20,790
and bring the series to a
supreme and conclusive end!

37
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:23,570
You got a serial in Weekly Manday?

38
00:01:23,740 --> 00:01:24,650
Amazing!

39
00:01:24,650 --> 00:01:27,270
You've joined the ranks of top
manga illustrators, Nonomura-sensei.

40
00:01:27,270 --> 00:01:28,710
The pay! How much do you make?!

41
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:30,380
Is that an appropriate question?

42
00:01:30,380 --> 00:01:31,330
You're so lucky.

43
00:01:31,330 --> 00:01:32,860
You'll be super rich now.

44
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:35,100
Freelance Investigator
Umemoto Kurumi

45
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:36,100
Plus, you get monthly compensation
from your ex-husband.

46
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:39,910
About that, he hasn't been depositing
the compensation fee lately.

47
00:01:39,910 --> 00:01:40,400
What?

48
00:01:40,610 --> 00:01:41,270
Really?

49
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:42,940
That's quite common.

50
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:44,650
Temp
Shinozuka Rina

51
00:01:42,940 --> 00:01:44,360
When compensation gets divided
into monthly payments,

52
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:46,230
those men eventually fade out.

53
00:01:46,230 --> 00:01:48,680
But even if you grow in
popularity, even if you get rich,

54
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,260
you have to make him keep paying.

55
00:01:50,260 --> 00:01:51,320
That's right.

56
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:54,160
You can never get enough income.

57
00:01:52,990 --> 00:01:56,390
Office landlord
Toyama Yoshie

58
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:57,110
I'll teach you how to rent out apartments!

59
00:01:57,310 --> 00:02:00,660
Well, to tell you the truth,
I'm still hesitant.

60
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:02,550
If I have to do a weekly serial,

61
00:02:02,550 --> 00:02:05,800
I'd be too busy to continue
working here.

62
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:06,730
What?

63
00:02:06,730 --> 00:02:08,170
Why are you hesitating about that?

64
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:09,050
That's right.

65
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:11,400
You should dump this place.
The faster, the better!

66
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:14,450
We don't get paid consistently, either.

67
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,800
I know, but...

68
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:21,220
Attorney
Hakamada Yukio

69
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:21,950
Anyway, let's celebrate
Kanae-chan's promotion today.

70
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:23,270
Sensei, pour some sake!

71
00:02:23,270 --> 00:02:27,220
Wait...
Yoshie-san, not so fast, please!

72
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:30,050
I haven't received
Hakamada-sensei's permission, yet.

73
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:31,800
You have my complete approval.

74
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,220
What?

75
00:02:32,810 --> 00:02:34,910
You were once my client,

76
00:02:34,910 --> 00:02:38,130
but you carved out a path for yourself,
and are about to begin a new life.

77
00:02:38,650 --> 00:02:40,500
What better news can there be?

78
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:42,770
Come on, Kanae-chan. Drink up.

79
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:53,410
Sensei, my glass is empty.

80
00:02:53,410 --> 00:02:54,440
Sorry.

81
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:58,040
Hurry up. Sensei, why aren't
you drinking, too?

82
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:59,320
I can't drink.

83
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:01,820
You're seriously a bore of
a man, you know that?

84
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,750
Sensei, how come you never got married?

85
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:11,290
If you're not drinking, at least
entertain me with stories or something.

86
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:13,370
Kanae-chan, maybe you shouldn't...

87
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:16,610
Well, I've never felt the
need to get married...

88
00:03:16,610 --> 00:03:19,240
Be honest. Tell the truth, would you?

89
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:20,980
Keep it coming.

90
00:03:23,050 --> 00:03:24,430
Wait, I know!

91
00:03:24,430 --> 00:03:25,990
You're gay? Gay?

92
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,210
No, I'm not!

93
00:03:26,210 --> 00:03:28,260
I knew it! He's gay!

94
00:03:28,670 --> 00:03:32,030
If they're busy, I can come back later.

95
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:35,000
Oh... one moment please.

96
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:38,190
Kanae's ex-husband
Kurasawa Yoshihito

97
00:03:35,910 --> 00:03:38,190
Cheers!

98
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:42,460
You know, it's because he's seen
so many failures come through his office.

99
00:03:42,460 --> 00:03:43,850
"Failures"?

100
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,510
What?

101
00:03:46,130 --> 00:03:47,300
Were you talking about me?

102
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:49,220
No, I didn't say anything about you.

103
00:03:49,220 --> 00:03:52,020
Sure, my marriage was a failure.

104
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:56,270
But I chalked it up to experience,
you understand?

105
00:03:56,270 --> 00:04:00,950
How could I have known that
husband was an adulterer?

106
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:03,000
Sensei, please come with me.

107
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,820
Oh, yes!

108
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:07,190
You can't escape me, Hakamada!

109
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:10,070
We have a client.

110
00:04:10,070 --> 00:04:10,920
A client?

111
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:14,650
Y-Yoshihito-san?

112
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:16,160
It's been a while.

113
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:17,530
What are you doing here?

114
00:04:18,130 --> 00:04:19,400
Oh, well,

115
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:22,900
I work here now.

116
00:04:23,470 --> 00:04:27,730
Sorry I've been late on
compensation payments.

117
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,670
What?

118
00:04:29,810 --> 00:04:33,590
You came here to tell me that?

119
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:37,450
Actually, I came to consult
Hakamada-sensei today.

120
00:04:39,170 --> 00:04:40,120
Me?

121
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:50,720
Divorce Chaser
~Let's Turn Your Tears into Money~

122
00:04:51,060 --> 00:04:55,900
Divorce Chaser Episode 11
An unsurmountable crisis!!
A formidable attorney enters the scene

123
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:57,460
Hakamada-sensei.

124
00:04:58,250 --> 00:05:00,740
I apologize for having caused
you trouble in the past.

125
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:01,890
No...

126
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:05,150
So, what can I do for you?

127
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,590
Well...

128
00:05:08,940 --> 00:05:10,720
it's about another
compensation lawsuit.

129
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:12,480
Compensation?

130
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:13,880
That guy never learns.

131
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:15,040
He must've cheated again.

132
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,780
He's sick, that's all. Sick.

133
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:19,930
He's truly divorce material.

134
00:05:20,170 --> 00:05:21,340
Right, Kanae-san?

135
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:26,080
Um...

136
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:29,460
It wasn't me who was cheating.

137
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:31,250
You heard us?

138
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:32,520
Sorry.

139
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,980
The one caught cheating was...

140
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,580
my wife, Shiori.

141
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,300
Shiori-san...

142
00:05:44,210 --> 00:05:47,310
Yoshihito's wife
Kurasawa Shiori

143
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:45,330
How do you do.

144
00:05:45,330 --> 00:05:47,780
Soon after my divorce with Kanae was official,

145
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:49,980
we legalized our union.

146
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:52,610
But I had a monthly
compensation fee to pay,

147
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:55,970
and couldn't afford to give her
the kind of life she expected.

148
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:58,370
Do you like this? Isn't it cute?

149
00:05:58,810 --> 00:05:59,840
How much was it?

150
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:02,250
It was on sale. It wasn't much.

151
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:03,210
About 50,000 yen.

152
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:06,900
Didn't I tell you we don't have
that kind of money right now?

153
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:11,470
Oh. Sorry.

154
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:15,590
Eventually cracks started
showing in our marriage.

155
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,590
I'm home.

156
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:32,820
I'm going to a dinner party with friends tonight!!

157
00:06:34,330 --> 00:06:38,860
And then, I received an envelope
with a letter from a lawyer.

158
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:46,200
Compensation lawsuit for damages
incurred from illicit activities

159
00:06:44,890 --> 00:06:47,240
Shiori was accused of
illicit activities.

160
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,670
illicit activities

161
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:51,240
3 million yen in damages

162
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:50,950
Three million yen in compensation?!

163
00:06:50,950 --> 00:06:51,700
Yes.

164
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:55,020
My wife's illicit partner had a wife.

165
00:06:55,630 --> 00:06:59,120
It was the wife who filed
the lawsuit against Shiori.

166
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:00,620
Is that what you call
a double-adultery?

167
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:03,240
Your wife never learns.

168
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:06,780
She's the kind who wants
what she can't have.

169
00:07:06,910 --> 00:07:10,060
Has Shiori-san admitted
to illicit activity?

170
00:07:11,060 --> 00:07:11,830
Yes.

171
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:13,380
Yeah.

172
00:07:14,090 --> 00:07:15,220
I did it.

173
00:07:17,130 --> 00:07:18,840
What were you thinking?

174
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,630
It's all your fault.

175
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:27,810
Our married life wasn't what
you promised it would be.

176
00:07:29,230 --> 00:07:30,340
Shiori!

177
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:33,310
My wife moved in with
her parents after that.

178
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,290
We're living separately now.

179
00:07:36,010 --> 00:07:36,900
I see.

180
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,150
We have no savings,

181
00:07:41,130 --> 00:07:43,420
or any means of paying
for compensation, either.

182
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:48,230
I was wondering if you
could help me somehow.

183
00:07:48,990 --> 00:07:51,590
Are you sure you
want me to help you?

184
00:07:52,690 --> 00:07:54,010
After all, I'm the one

185
00:07:54,010 --> 00:07:55,830
who slapped you with an
exorbitant lawsuit in the first place.

186
00:07:56,740 --> 00:08:00,240
Actually, it was because of that,
that I am now seeking your help.

187
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:08,930
We're scheduled for a talk with the
other party's legal representative soon.

188
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:14,120
I was hoping you could
sit in on the session.

189
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:24,800
Hakamada Law Office

190
00:08:24,930 --> 00:08:25,900
Today's the day.

191
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,000
Of what?

192
00:08:27,170 --> 00:08:29,350
You know, the meeting with your ex-husband.

193
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,910
The other lawyer's
coming here today, too.

194
00:08:31,910 --> 00:08:33,030
I see.

195
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,750
Kanae-san, are you okay with this?

196
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,130
With what?

197
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:43,670
Hakamada-sensei is going to represent
your ex-husband's obnoxious wife.

198
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:47,660
That's Hakamada-sensei's
decision to make, not mine.

199
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:55,380
Excuse us.

200
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,300
You don't have to hide.

201
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,540
Good to have you here.

202
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:04,830
Please come this way.

203
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,700
Huh?

204
00:09:06,710 --> 00:09:08,040
This is your lawyer?

205
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:09,690
It has been a while.

206
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:11,410
I'm Hakamada, attorney at law.

207
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:13,380
Wait a second, here.

208
00:09:13,770 --> 00:09:15,220
Why's it have to be this guy?

209
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:16,840
Huh?

210
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:25,550
And what's your ex-wife doing here?

211
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:28,700
Well... she's been working here.

212
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,790
You've been seeing your ex, huh?

213
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:32,650
And you have the nerve
to berate me for cheating.

214
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:34,770
That's not how it is, Shiori.

215
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:38,730
Before we have our discussion
with the other party's attorney,

216
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:41,460
I have a few questions for Shiori-san.

217
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:43,720
I have nothing to say to you.

218
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,470
Huh?

219
00:09:45,430 --> 00:09:49,180
Our married life was ruined
because of this guy.

220
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:51,800
Can't we find another lawyer?

221
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:54,610
Hakamada-sensei is
an outstanding lawyer.

222
00:09:54,830 --> 00:09:56,860
He's on our side now.

223
00:09:57,350 --> 00:10:00,230
Your ex-wife is working
at this office, too, right?

224
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:03,920
She might sabotage us out of revenge.

225
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,950
No, that kind of thing will not happen.

226
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,900
Anyway, I refuse.

227
00:10:09,390 --> 00:10:13,960
I'd rather pay the lawsuit
and get divorced.

228
00:10:15,050 --> 00:10:18,150
I want a fresh start,
as soon as possible.

229
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,110
Pardon me.

230
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:32,340
Oh, yes?

231
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,550
I am Honjo Yayoi-san's
legal representative,

232
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:36,090
Karasuma Keiko.

233
00:10:40,630 --> 00:10:41,870
Hakamada-san?

234
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:45,740
It's you, isn't it, Hakamada-san?

235
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:48,890
It has been a while.

236
00:10:50,330 --> 00:10:53,960
Even when I heard "Hakamada Law Office,"
I never expected...

237
00:10:54,330 --> 00:10:56,270
But, you're still practicing law.

238
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:58,330
You know each other?

239
00:10:58,880 --> 00:10:59,610
Yes.

240
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:01,110
Sort of.

241
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:04,490
Sieg Law Office attorney
Karasuma Keiko

242
00:11:01,550 --> 00:11:05,480
We worked at the same law firm
before I went solo.

243
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:08,180
You were very kind to me, then.

244
00:11:09,330 --> 00:11:11,910
You were a corporate lawyer, too?

245
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:13,290
Yes.

246
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:16,230
In fact, I still specialize
in corporate law.

247
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:20,030
I'm the in-house attorney
for Honjo Industries

248
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:23,180
presided over by my client,
Honjo Takashi-san,

249
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:25,850
who has requested that
I represent his wife in this case.

250
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,290
Hakamada-sensei,

251
00:11:27,620 --> 00:11:28,850
I look forward to working with you.

252
00:11:33,310 --> 00:11:35,720
Hakamada
Law Office

253
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,710
Will your client be joining us today?

254
00:11:36,210 --> 00:11:37,460
Yayoi-san

255
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,730
suffered a physical breakdown after she
discovered her husband's affair.

256
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:42,490
She will not be joining us today.

257
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,900
I see.

258
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:45,280
Kanae-san.

259
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,660
You're curious, aren't you?

260
00:11:47,990 --> 00:11:49,030
No, not really.

261
00:11:49,610 --> 00:11:51,880
I'm going to go hunt for material.

262
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:54,280
Well then, to begin...

263
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:55,960
please have a look.

