We all know who will win, anyway.

528
00:32:16,460 --> 00:32:17,740
Thank you for waiting.

529
00:32:17,900 --> 00:32:18,830
On another note,

530
00:32:19,890 --> 00:32:21,620
would you be interested
in joining our firm?

531
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:25,040
You have some nerve, asking me that.

532
00:32:25,460 --> 00:32:26,880
Come on, Hakamada-san.

533
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:29,990
You didn't become a lawyer
to handle divorce cases, right?

534
00:32:30,340 --> 00:32:33,060
It's a lot of tedious
work with little payoff.

535
00:32:33,410 --> 00:32:36,600
Oh, and I did a background
check of your office.

536
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:39,480
About two or three clients per month...

537
00:32:40,050 --> 00:32:42,830
After deducting all expenses,
you must be flat broke.

538
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:46,020
If you join our firm,

539
00:32:46,470 --> 00:32:48,240
you'll make ten times
what you're making now.

540
00:32:48,610 --> 00:32:50,230
That is, judging by your ability.

541
00:32:51,570 --> 00:32:55,480
I don't practice law for the money.

542
00:32:56,520 --> 00:32:58,200
What do you do it for, then?

543
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:02,200
Oh, yes. I remember what you
said a long time ago...

544
00:33:02,700 --> 00:33:04,780
"The work of the attorney is
to walk in your clients' shoes,

545
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:10,170
and discover the best
ways to help them."

546
00:33:11,590 --> 00:33:16,170
But can you say the same for
clients with malicious intent?

547
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:20,290
Lawyers can't choose their clients.

548
00:33:20,930 --> 00:33:25,370
We are obligated to protect even
those we'd rather not protect.

549
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,440
Justice is a relative thing.

550
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:34,440
Therefore our sole concern
is whether we win or lose.

551
00:33:36,230 --> 00:33:39,290
There's no justice beyond that concern.

552
00:33:44,290 --> 00:33:45,460
Are you...

553
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:49,670
still holding a grudge from that time?

554
00:33:52,790 --> 00:33:55,030
I was desperate, then.

555
00:33:55,410 --> 00:33:57,830
I wanted to further my career a lawyer.

556
00:33:58,890 --> 00:33:59,720
But...

557
00:34:00,700 --> 00:34:02,500
When it came to you,

558
00:34:02,500 --> 00:34:05,280
it wasn't like I got close to you
just to use you.

559
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:08,520
My feelings for you were genuine—

560
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:09,760
Let's not talk about that.

561
00:34:13,010 --> 00:34:13,840
Anyway,

562
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:16,810
drop by our office if you want a job.

563
00:34:24,050 --> 00:34:24,700
Um...

564
00:34:24,900 --> 00:34:25,960
Excuse me.

565
00:34:26,850 --> 00:34:28,570
That lady who was with you?

566
00:34:28,930 --> 00:34:30,410
She left without paying.

567
00:34:34,140 --> 00:34:36,540
Hakamada Law Office

568
00:34:44,170 --> 00:34:45,960
Where were you?

569
00:34:47,990 --> 00:34:50,500
I should ask you. What are
you doing here so late?

570
00:34:51,810 --> 00:34:53,640
Waiting for you, Hakamada-sensei.

571
00:34:54,700 --> 00:34:55,520
Waiting for me?

572
00:35:01,450 --> 00:35:04,960
Please don't turn Yoshihito-san down.

573
00:35:05,730 --> 00:35:06,890
As I have already explained,

574
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:08,570
he doesn't stand a chance.

575
00:35:08,890 --> 00:35:11,770
Is that because your opponent
is Karasuma Keiko-san?

576
00:35:13,650 --> 00:35:16,930
Yoshie-san told me about
your past history with her.

577
00:35:18,930 --> 00:35:20,420
She did it again...

578
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:24,520
Are you going to compromise your
fortitude for something like that?

579
00:35:26,710 --> 00:35:28,430
This isn't like you.

580
00:35:28,430 --> 00:35:31,200
You have always put yourself
in your clients' shoes, always!

581
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:33,840
Then you'd always find the
best ways to help them.

582
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:35,660
But not this time around.

583
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:38,970
The opposing lawyer was your ex,

584
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:39,980
so you're cowering and running away!

585
00:35:39,980 --> 00:35:41,740
You're just trying to
protect yourself!

586
00:35:41,740 --> 00:35:42,860
That is not true.

587
00:35:42,860 --> 00:35:44,370
Why did you refuse him, then?!

588
00:35:45,100 --> 00:35:47,140
Because he doesn't stand a chance?

589
00:35:47,140 --> 00:35:48,860
Those aren't Hakamada-sensei's words.

590
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:58,010
I read this month's issue.

591
00:35:59,810 --> 00:36:02,490
The protagonist's crisis
in the story is trite.

592
00:36:02,900 --> 00:36:03,560
What?

593
00:36:03,660 --> 00:36:07,800
It makes me wonder if you can
handle a weekly serial.

594
00:36:08,730 --> 00:36:10,120
Now, how did that feel,

595
00:36:10,310 --> 00:36:12,260
to hear an opinion from
an absolute amateur?

596
00:36:13,450 --> 00:36:15,330
You're doing the same thing to me.

597
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:19,020
If you have time to be
concerned about my work,

598
00:36:19,540 --> 00:36:22,010
you should be getting ready
for your weekly serials instead.

599
00:36:23,250 --> 00:36:24,420
I don't want to hear the opinions

600
00:36:24,940 --> 00:36:26,620
of someone getting ready to quit.

601
00:36:28,890 --> 00:36:29,980
Understood.

602
00:36:30,580 --> 00:36:32,720
But before I quit,

603
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:35,490
I'm going to take over
this case, and settle it.

604
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:39,520
There's nothing
that you could do.

605
00:36:40,900 --> 00:36:45,430
I have been watching you
work for a whole year now.

606
00:36:46,250 --> 00:36:49,320
I know the methods you've
used to help your clients.

607
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:50,850
I know them very well.

608
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:55,820
So, I'm going to help that client,

609
00:36:55,820 --> 00:36:57,630
the way that you would do it.

610
00:37:12,250 --> 00:37:13,340
Sorry to say,

611
00:37:13,980 --> 00:37:16,210
but I agree with Kanae-chan's opinion.

612
00:37:17,610 --> 00:37:19,440
The way you've been lately,
Hakamada-sensei...

613
00:37:20,190 --> 00:37:22,720
is not like Hakamada-sensei at all.

614
00:37:23,830 --> 00:37:26,860
Not only have you not put
yourself in your client's shoes...

615
00:37:27,230 --> 00:37:30,780
You don't even understand
Kanae-san's feelings, do you?

616
00:37:33,660 --> 00:37:34,880
What do you mean?

617
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:38,950
Kanae-san turned down
the weekly syndication.

618
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:41,590
Why?

619
00:37:42,170 --> 00:37:45,780
She said she didn't want to discontinue
the monthly Divorce Chaser manga.

620
00:37:47,170 --> 00:37:49,370
To succeed as a manga illustrator,

621
00:37:49,370 --> 00:37:51,970
weekly serials are the fastest track.

622
00:37:53,380 --> 00:37:54,220
Instead,

623
00:37:55,030 --> 00:37:59,740
she said she wants share what
she learns at this law office,

624
00:37:59,740 --> 00:38:01,750
with all her readers.

625
00:38:04,260 --> 00:38:06,000
She wants to help people, too,

626
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:10,360
using whatever means
she has at her disposal.

627
00:38:12,140 --> 00:38:15,600
In the same way that you
hepled her, Hakamada-sensei.

628
00:38:17,070 --> 00:38:23,880
Kanae-chan must be pulling out
her hair, seeing you like this.

629
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:47,880
You will pay the
compensation!

630
00:38:45,150 --> 00:38:47,880
Of all the men
I have ever met ...

631
00:38:45,150 --> 00:38:47,880
you are a "dumb man"
of the highest order.

632
00:38:50,790 --> 00:38:54,160
And yet, notwithstanding, you haven't
asked Kanae-san's forgiveness,

633
00:38:54,790 --> 00:38:56,070
not even once.

634
00:38:57,560 --> 00:39:00,130
I have no intention of lessening the
compensation for a person like you.

635
00:39:00,290 --> 00:39:04,430
Ichikawa-san. You truly
are in pain, correct?

636
00:39:04,890 --> 00:39:05,550
Yes.

637
00:39:06,040 --> 00:39:06,930
In that case,

638
00:39:08,220 --> 00:39:10,740
it is only proper we
demand compensation.

639
00:39:21,700 --> 00:39:25,450
You're nothing but a third-rate
ambulance chaser!

640
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:25,450
I have representation by a first-rate law firm, you're in for a treat!

641
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:25,030
Can you stand living
with him as you have,

642
00:39:25,770 --> 00:39:28,200
for the next 25 years?

643
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:29,180
I can't do it.

644
00:39:29,530 --> 00:39:30,690
In that case,

645
00:39:31,250 --> 00:39:32,730
all we can do is forge ahead.

646
00:39:34,400 --> 00:39:36,230
The total membership fees
and compensation...

647
00:39:37,090 --> 00:39:38,120
you will pay, won't you?

648
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:41,380
After all, you shallowly judge
people based on appearances...

649
00:39:42,050 --> 00:39:44,700
you're not qualified to
oversee human encounters.

650
00:39:47,570 --> 00:39:53,850
I never turn anyone down
if they are truly in need.

651
00:39:55,370 --> 00:39:58,200
You have always put yourself
in your clients' shoes, always.

652
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,760
Then you'd always find the
best ways to help them.

653
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:02,850
Because he doesn't stand a chance?

654
00:40:02,850 --> 00:40:04,520
Those aren't Hakamada-sensei's words.

655
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:24,340
I'm glad you came, Hakamada-san.

656
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:26,210
Thank you for yesterday.

657
00:40:26,730 --> 00:40:28,360
Since you're here,

658
00:40:28,360 --> 00:40:30,000
I assume you're accepting my offer?

659
00:40:30,890 --> 00:40:31,650
No.

660
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,530
With regard to the offer,

661
00:40:33,530 --> 00:40:35,290
I respectfully decline.

662
00:40:36,050 --> 00:40:36,820
What?

663
00:40:37,750 --> 00:40:39,860
I came here today because there
is something I want to tell you.

664
00:40:41,650 --> 00:40:43,730
And what could that be?

665
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:50,600
First of all, please give me 1,200 yen.

666
00:40:50,810 --> 00:40:51,460
Huh?

667
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:54,380
That's the charge for the
glass of wine you drank.

668
00:40:56,760 --> 00:40:59,250
It's fine to put on airs
and walk out of the bar...

669
00:40:59,770 --> 00:41:03,630
but you should pay for
your own beverages.

670
00:41:03,630 --> 00:41:06,310
Still as petty as ever...

671
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:14,960
And I believe we will be suing
your client, Honjo Yayoi-san's husband,

672
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:18,920
Honjo Takashi-san.

673
00:41:19,630 --> 00:41:21,020
Are you joking?

674
00:41:21,810 --> 00:41:23,630
You don't stand a chance.

675
00:41:23,810 --> 00:41:25,940
A lawyer who turns down clients

676
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:27,820
because he believes he
doesn't stand a chance...

677
00:41:27,820 --> 00:41:29,670
is not a lawyer in my books.

678
00:41:33,140 --> 00:41:35,050
I know I'm overstepping
my bounds, but...

679
00:41:38,770 --> 00:41:40,410
you should be prepared to lose.

680
00:41:45,620 --> 00:41:46,630
Your change.

681
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:56,900
The shocking final episode

682
00:41:56,900 --> 00:42:05,570
Next episode

683
00:41:57,100 --> 00:41:58,590
I am prepared
for disbarment.

684
00:41:58,590 --> 00:42:00,450
Now that it's gone to court,

685
00:41:58,970 --> 00:42:02,070
The final battle, laying his life as an attorney on the line

686
00:42:00,450 --> 00:42:01,880
there's no way you can win.

687
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:03,630
Damn, she got us good.

688
00:42:02,100 --> 00:42:05,670
What will be Hakamada Yukio's fate?!

689
00:42:03,630 --> 00:42:06,080
I won't take
this lying down.

690
00:42:05,740 --> 00:42:09,440
This drama is a work of fiction

691
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:08,820
Now, let me make a counterargument.

